rComments: Monotone teaching, however his assignments & exams are really easy - with the exception of a few tricky questions, they are mostly directly out of the textbook. It's hard to pay attention in his classes but you might learn the RL-applications if you do! Also he may cancel his lectures at the last minute, watch out for that.

Prof Ragheb is actually quite monotone in his explanations, but he is a very nice guy! The class is interesting and the exams and assignments are very easy. Exams are open-book and you can even bring the corrected assignments. Average was an A at the end. Just take this class and allow yourself some breathing space.
